  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Accepted, W-CON-01)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; twelve carry structured requiredLevel and achievedLevel integers. One factor — Model form — is documented through a richly written qualitative assessment in lieu of structured level assignments, reflecting the assessor team's judgment that the hemolysis constitutive model warrants narrative treatment given the absence of standardised gradation criteria for non-Newtonian power-law damage models. The overall package decision is Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
